name: Derwent Block M (opposite Courtyard
directions:
Coming from University Road: Head for the department for education and enter the automatic door in the corner of the small car park.  Do not enter the reception for the Department for Education, once through the big automatic door, turn immediately left, head through the concertina doors and continue about 4 / 5 metres.  There is a blue and glass door on the right that opens outwards.  Pass through the door and the toilet, labelled 'toilet' is on the immediate right!

Coming from the Wayfinder and Courtyard, head to the outside decked area of Courtyard and go up the ranp parallel to the decked area of Courtyard.  There is a blue and glass door on the left that opens outwards, go through and the toilet is immediately on the right!
comment: Turn the light OFF as the window is not the best at providing privacy!!

name: Pilgrim River Steakhouse
directions: The restroom is to the left of the “please wait to be seated” area.
comment:
Since it’s right by the waiting area and is a fancier restaurant, just going to the bathroom and leaving will probably get you some judgement. I’d suggest only use this restroom if you are planning on dining here.

That said, the restroom is spacious and clean. And it’s a rare one that has a changing table! :)

www.Trans.health

name: Any of the little white and blue trailer houses.
directions: The little trailer houses 50-100 yard away from the school.
comment:
The little white and blue trailer houses have gender neutral restrooms. Just ask the current renters if you could use their bathroom and offer to sanitize the toilet after use. They will say yes to you using the restroom and will let you off from cleaning.
The school DOES have gendered bathrooms but people don’t really care which one you use as long as you wash your hands. (They didn’t allow this when I was going to school here but they do allow it now)
